{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:04:27.754939+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's a walkthrough of the three database migrations in this repository, in the order they'd be applied:\n\n---\n\n### Migration 1: `001_create_users.sql`\n**Creates the `users` table**\n\n| Column | Type | Constraints |\n|---|---|---|\n| `id` | `BIGSERIAL` | `PRIMARY KEY` |\n| `email` | `TEXT` | `UNIQUE NOT NULL` |\n| `display_name` | `TEXT` | (nullable) |\n| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ` | `NOT NULL DEFAULT now()` |\n\nThis is the foundational user table. It uses an auto-incrementing 64-bit integer primary key, enforces unique email addresses, stores an optional display name, and timestamps each row at creation time.\n\n---\n\n### Migration 2: `002_create_sessions.sql`\n**Creates the `sessions` table**\n\n| Column | Type | Constraints |\n|---|---|---|\n| `id` | `UUID` | `PRIMARY KEY` |\n| `user_id` | `BIGINT` | `NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE` |\n| `issued_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ` | `NOT NULL DEFAULT now()` |\n| `expires_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ` | `NOT NULL` |\n\nThis table stores user sessions. Each session has a UUID as its primary key, a foreign key to `users(id)` with cascade delete (so deleting a user automatically removes their sessions), and tracks when the session was issued and when it expires. This depends on migration 001 for the `users` table.\n\n---\n\n### Migration 3: `003_add_session_index.sql`\n**Adds an index on `sessions(user_id)`**\n\n```sql\nCREATE INDEX idx_sessions_user_id ON sessions(user_id);\n```\n\nThis is a performance optimization. It creates a B-tree index on the `user_id` foreign key column of the `sessions` table, speeding up lookups of all sessions belonging to a particular user — a very common query in session-based authentication flows.\n\n---\n\n### Order of Application\nMigrations follow a strict numeric ordering: **001 → 002 → 003**. This is the standard convention (e.g., for tools like `golang-migrate`, Flyway, or hand-rolled runners) where migrations are sorted lexicographically or numerically by filename prefix and applied in that sequence.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 827, "prompt_tokens": 5180, "total_tokens": 6007, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 321, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 4864}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 4864, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 316}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "c5bc689e-c4b2-4b2c-b486-1c2f5c74ca2c", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3e6-9a73-7e51-97a6-b841a2531fc3-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 5180, "output_tokens": 827, "total_tokens": 6007, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 4864}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 321}}}}]}}}
